Detailed Description

cvmx_lmc::_dual_memcfg

This register controls certain parameters of dual-memory configuration.

This register enables the design to have two separate memory configurations, selected dynamically by the reference address. Note however, that both configurations share LMC()_CONTROL[XOR_BANK], LMC()_CONFIG [PBANK_LSB], LMC()_CONFIG[RANK_ENA], and all timing parameters.

In this description: * config0 refers to the normal memory configuration that is defined by the LMC()_CONFIG[ROW_LSB] parameter * config1 refers to the dual (or second) memory configuration that is defined by this register.
